This paper discusses the semantics of type classes in Haskell, which is a topic related to programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the behavior of programs, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to interpreting polymorphic expressions, which could be relevant to programming language theory and programming language implementation (cs.TPLP, cs.FL).
